{
  "doc_id": "24630",
  "text": "Histochemical detection of GUS activity was carried out by incubating plants or plant parts for 4-18 h in 0.5 mM X-gluc (5-bromo-4-chloro-3-indolyl-b-D-glucopyranoside) in a buffer containing 50 mM Na-phosphate, pH 7.0, and 0.1% Triton X-100 (Jefferson et al. 1987; [CITATION_1] . Chlorophyll was cleared through several changes of 70% ethanol. Digital images were captured directly with a camera or with a light microscope using brightfield or darkfield optics.",
